ference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_A._Steitz#cite_note-Tom_Steitz-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> \"for his studies on the structure and function of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ribosome\" title=\"Ribosome\">ribosome<\/a> which showed that the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Peptide\" title=\"Peptide\">peptidyl<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Transferase\" title=\"Transferase\">transferase<\/a> was an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/RNA\" title=\"RNA\">RNA<\/a> catalyzed reaction, and for revealing the mechanism of inhibition of this function by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Antibiotics\" title=\"Antibiotics\">antibiotics<\/a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_A._Steitz#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Thomas A. Steitz","place_of_birth":"Milwaukee ,  Wisconsin","place_of_death":null,"text":"Thomas A. Steitz , Chemistry, 2009","year":2009.0}